Wow this was delicious. This was the main dish in a 4 course asian seafood dinner for my stepdad's birthday and was a MASSIVE HIT with everyone. Great flavours, great textures, and little preparation time. We used black cod instead of bass, and used very wide bowls so that the panko on the fish would just sit on top of the mushrooms and stay crispy, as opposed to sinking into the broth and getting soggy. What a fantastic dish.

